04:32.074 --> 04:34.855
<i>a little after the fourth birthday.</i>

04:34.891 --> 04:36.690
Oh! Oh, this is easy.

04:36.726 --> 04:39.427
Not a sheep. Another type of sheep.

04:39.462 --> 04:40.928
- Your time's running out.
- Lamb? Goat?

04:40.963 --> 04:42.062
- Yes!
- Nice.

04:42.097 --> 04:44.977
Toboni: <i>How did your
family and friends respond</i>

04:45.002 --> 04:46.300
<i>to Kai transitioning?</i>

04:46.335 --> 04:49.403
I had come from a
really large, Southern,

04:49.438 --> 04:52.039
you know, Republican, Christian family.

04:52.074 --> 04:54.313
All of my friends...

04:54.509 --> 04:56.743
uh, were in ministry.

04:56.778 --> 04:59.336
Strong, devout Christians.

04:59.881 --> 05:02.816
Straight-ticket Republicans like I was.

05:02.851 --> 05:05.418
So, we immediately started

05:05.454 --> 05:07.654
losing nearly every friend,

05:07.689 --> 05:10.836
and every close and meaningful
relationship that we had.

05:10.861 --> 05:15.361
How does it feel to lose
90 percent of your family

05:15.396 --> 05:17.535
because your child is transgender?

05:18.834 --> 05:20.899
(voice breaking) It feels lonely.

05:23.537 --> 05:25.571
You feel like...

05:27.675 --> 05:31.060
you're in the fight of your life...

05:33.375 --> 05:36.043
to save your child.

05:36.250 --> 05:40.098
And the people that
have been in your life...

05:40.331 --> 05:43.879
they leave you on the battlefield alone.

05:46.694 --> 05:48.906
<i>How do you do that to Kai?</i>

05:49.262 --> 05:51.763
There are a lot of people in
the world that hate my child

05:51.799 --> 05:54.187
simply because she exists.

05:54.834 --> 05:58.803
Toboni: <i>Around 1.7 percent of American
youth identify as transgender,</i>

05:58.828 --> 06:00.553
<i>and those estimates are conservative,</i>

06:00.578 --> 06:03.170
<i>since the population is
likely under-reporting.</i>

06:03.195 --> 06:05.444
<i>Today, these trans
students find themselves</i>

06:05.469 --> 06:08.515
<i>at the center of a national
debate over bathroom laws.</i>

06:08.593 --> 06:11.539
Breaking tonight: A firestorm
of criticism continues to build

06:11.574 --> 06:15.043
24 hours after the White
House drops a late-night memo

06:15.078 --> 06:17.545
changing the rules at
every school in America

06:17.580 --> 06:20.507
when it comes to the issue
of transgender students.

06:20.532 --> 06:21.849
Toboni: <i>In May of last year,</i>

06:21.874 --> 06:24.351
<i>the White House issued a
directive to public schools</i>

06:24.387 --> 06:25.987
<i>to allow students to use the bathroom</i>

06:26.022 --> 06:27.687
<i>matching their gender identity,</i>

06:27.712 --> 06:30.052
<i>or risk losing federal funding.</i>

06:30.077 --> 06:32.663
<i>In response, Texas led a dozen states</i>

06:32.688 --> 06:35.171
<i>in suing the federal
government over the guidance.</i>

06:35.196 --> 06:36.697
<i>Ten more states followed.</i>

06:36.732 --> 06:40.066
If this prevails, this'll be the
end of public schools as we know it.

06:40.091 --> 06:42.229
Kimberly: <i>Most of the
leadership in Texas,</i>

06:42.254 --> 06:46.299
have come out and made strong stands
against the transgender community.

06:46.324 --> 06:50.715
<i>The school district has an
ultraconservative school board,</i>

06:50.785 --> 06:54.414
<i>and an ultraconservative superintendent.</i>

06:54.449 --> 06:58.135
We are probably in the
worst school district,

06:58.160 --> 07:01.456
in the worst state
right now at this time,

07:01.481 --> 07:03.401
starting kindergarten.

07:04.859 --> 07:07.159
Toboni: <i>With kindergarten
less than two weeks away,</i>

07:07.195 --> 07:09.362
<i>Kimberly is heading to her
local school board meeting</i>

07:09.397 --> 07:12.507
<i>to fight for Kai to be able
to use the girls' bathroom.</i>

07:12.532 --> 07:15.901
All: One nation, under God, indivisible,

07:15.937 --> 07:18.629
with liberty and justice for all.

07:18.654 --> 07:22.690
Woman: Next on the agenda,
we have Miss Shappley?

07:22.715 --> 07:25.454
♪ ♪

07:25.479 --> 07:27.780
Dear Board Members, my
name is Kimberly Shappley,

07:27.815 --> 07:31.384
and I am the parent of a
transgender student here in PISD.

07:31.409 --> 07:33.518
Toboni: <i>As soon as
Kimberly started speaking,</i>

07:33.554 --> 07:37.055
<i>the superintendent and several
audience members left the room.</i>

07:37.090 --> 07:40.825
Kimberly: The suicide rate for a
transgender youth is 41 percent.

07:40.861 --> 07:44.062
That is why we are fighting so
adamantly for these children.

07:44.089 --> 07:46.626
I propose that transgender
students be allowed

07:46.651 --> 07:48.533
to use the restroom which corresponds

07:48.569 --> 07:50.769
to their gender identity,
and allow students

07:50.804 --> 07:52.766
whose parents do not want them to use

07:52.791 --> 07:55.070
the same restroom as a trans student,

07:55.095 --> 07:57.996
use the alternate
facility that's supplied.

07:58.021 --> 08:01.139
That way, my child won't remember
anything about discrimination

08:01.164 --> 08:03.181
from her first year of public school,

08:03.216 --> 08:04.734
and 30 years from now,

08:04.759 --> 08:06.917
students whose parents
chose to segregate them

08:06.952 --> 08:10.588
will remember which side of civil
rights history their family was on.

08:10.623 --> 08:13.288
What I would like to say now
is, I am a mom of a little girl

08:13.313 --> 08:15.192
that I would like to see live.

08:15.227 --> 08:18.961
I am a mom of a little girl who
has a 41 percent suicide rate.

08:19.102 --> 08:21.532
That is a very real thing.

08:21.567 --> 08:24.534
Please understand, I'm not
fighting about bathrooms.

08:24.569 --> 08:26.242
I'm fighting about her life.

08:26.648 --> 08:28.371
Toboni: <i>The day before school started,</i>

08:28.407 --> 08:30.473
<i>a Texas judge temporarily blocked</i>

08:30.509 --> 08:31.966
<i>the White House directive.</i>

08:31.991 --> 08:35.427
<i>Meaning Kai isn't able to
use the girls' bathroom.</i>

08:35.778 --> 08:39.416
I pledge to every citizen of our land

08:39.451 --> 08:42.337
that I will be president
for all Americans.

08:42.363 --> 08:44.424
Toboni: <i>The election of
Donald Trump sent a shock wave</i>

08:44.449 --> 08:45.903
<i>through the trans community,</i>

08:45.928 --> 08:47.409
<i>and one month into office,</i>

08:47.434 --> 08:51.127
<i>he withdrew the Obama administration's
federal bathroom guidance.</i>

08:51.162 --> 08:53.029
<i>Former Attorney General Loretta Lynch</i>

08:53.064 --> 08:55.887
<i>has been a leading advocate
for the trans community.</i>

08:55.965 --> 08:58.598
Why should this be viewed
as a civil rights issue?

08:58.637 --> 09:00.231
Because this issue of how we treat

09:00.256 --> 09:02.190
transgender people in our community,

09:02.215 --> 09:06.479
in particular, how we treat
transgender students in our schools

09:06.504 --> 09:09.839
relates to how our government
is gonna interact with people

09:09.864 --> 09:11.714
whom we perceive to be different.

09:11.739 --> 09:13.281
We've made such great progress

09:13.317 --> 09:15.411
in so many areas of civil rights...

09:15.436 --> 09:17.786
uh, accepting people for who they are,

09:17.822 --> 09:20.018
and when you see that
attempt to roll back

09:20.043 --> 09:22.558
that change, through the use of the law,

09:22.593 --> 09:25.293
that's exactly when the Department
of Justice has to step in.

09:25.329 --> 09:28.094
One of the main opposing
arguments is that...

09:28.119 --> 09:31.951
predators could go into,
let's say, a girls' bathroom,

09:31.976 --> 09:35.470
making parents feel that their
children's safety is at risk.

09:35.505 --> 09:36.804
What is your response to that?

09:36.840 --> 09:38.840
Of course we want to
protect our children

09:38.876 --> 09:41.801
from people who are gonna prey on
them, in a bathroom, in a school.

09:41.826 --> 09:44.787
But that's not the basis
for the violence that we see

09:44.812 --> 09:46.458
directed against children.

09:46.483 --> 09:49.116
It's not coming from the
transgender community.

09:49.151 --> 09:51.429
The reality is, it's a sad reality,

09:51.454 --> 09:53.821
that transgender
individuals in this country

09:53.857 --> 09:56.657
are much more likely to
be the victims of violence

09:56.693 --> 09:58.426
than the perpetrators of violence.

09:58.461 --> 10:01.262
Is this more than about bathrooms?

10:01.297 --> 10:02.696
I think that it's more than bathrooms

10:02.731 --> 10:04.731
because it is about innate dignity.

10:04.767 --> 10:07.768
Adolescence is hard for any child.

10:07.803 --> 10:09.703
And you couple that with the issues

10:09.738 --> 10:12.907
of making sure that you're
comfortable and secure

10:12.942 --> 10:16.777
with your gender identity,
it adds an extra weight to it.

10:16.812 --> 10:19.245
This literally is a
matter of life and death

10:19.281 --> 10:23.459
for so many young people who are
dealing with these issues of identity.

10:23.519 --> 10:25.218
Toboni: <i>It's life or
death, because the rate</i>

10:25.253 --> 10:28.889
<i>of suicide attempts in the
trans community is 40 percent.</i>

10:29.287 --> 10:31.248
<i>As families try to
support their children</i>

10:31.273 --> 10:33.343
<i>and lessen the potential for self-harm,</i>

10:33.368 --> 10:35.241
<i>they're now forced to weigh the options</i>

10:35.266 --> 10:37.288
<i>of early medical intervention.</i>

10:37.365 --> 10:39.624
<i>Now kids, like
eight-year-old Max O'Brien,</i>

10:39.649 --> 10:41.667
<i>can delay the onset of puberty</i>

10:41.702 --> 10:44.337
<i>using drugs called "hormone blockers."</i>

10:44.372 --> 10:48.499
Max, when did you first
realize that you were a boy?

10:48.913 --> 10:51.710
I just thought I was
a boy my whole life.

10:51.746 --> 10:53.111
